OL,3,CMother wants extra support for parents
OL,4,Cof children with autism
OL,6,FWhen asked about her thoughts on how
OL,7,Fwell Guernsey's government caters for
OL,8,Fthe needs of neurodiverse children,
OL,9,FAntonia replies: "What's happening is
OL,10,Fthat you get diagnosed then you get
OL,11,Fleft. So yes, they've done a great job
OL,12,Fon actually getting kids diagnosed
OL,13,Fquicker. They've brought in off-island
OL,14,Fsupport but actually, then what
OL,15,Fhappens?"
OL,17,FThe Government brought in a UK-based
OL,18,Fcompany to address the rising demand
OL,19,Ffor diagnoses in March.
