OL,3,CMother wants extra support for parents
OL,4,Cof children with autism
OL,6,FITV News has approached the States of
OL,7,FGuernsey for a response to the issues
OL,8,Fraised.
OL,10,FNiamh McDermott from the charity
OL,11,FJersey Autism Support says businesses
OL,12,Fshould allow parents who care for
OL,13,Fneurodiverse children to have more
OL,14,Fflexible working arrangements.
OL,16,FShe also tellls ITV News that
OL,17,Femployers should be given basic
OL,18,Ftraining about neurodiversity and
OL,19,Fautism.
