OL,3,CMother wants extra support for parents
OL,4,Cof children with autism
OL,6,FNiamh, who is the parent of a child
OL,7,Fwith autism, says: "Parents like us,
OL,8,Fwe have to keep so much patience and
OL,9,Fenergy for our children so it's very
OL,10,Fhard to have that in other areas of
OL,11,Flife."
OL,13,FShe adds that seven years ago she had
OL,14,Fto quit her job after her neurodiverse
OL,15,Fchild was unable to access full-time
OL,16,Feducation and describes the experience
OL,17,Fas "very isolating" - she has also
OL,18,Fcalled for extra support for parents
OL,19,Fin Jersey.
